This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a weakly supervised instance segmentation algorithm based on deep learning. The paper also mentions the use of a unified deep neural network architecture, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves object detection and semantic segmentation, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a positive feedback loop and end-to-end trainability suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
